## One-Command Migration CLI

The fastest way to use aws2lakehouse — no Python code, no YAML to write manually.

### Basic Usage

```bash
# Migrate an AWS project to Databricks (one command)
python migrate.py --source ./aws-project --dest ./databricks-project

# With custom catalog and org name
python migrate.py --source ./aws-repo --dest ./dbx-repo --catalog production --org acme-capital

# Preview what would be generated (no files written)
python migrate.py --source ./aws-repo --dest ./dbx-repo --dry-run

# Enable AI-enhanced code transformation and documentation
python migrate.py --source ./aws-repo --dest ./dbx-repo --ai --ai-model opus

# Parallel AI calls for large migrations (4 threads)
python migrate.py --source ./aws-repo --dest ./dbx-repo --ai --threads 4

# Verbose mode (shows fallback warnings during parsing)
python migrate.py --source ./aws-repo --dest ./dbx-repo -v

# Clean destination before generating
python migrate.py --source ./aws-repo --dest ./dbx-repo --clean
```

### CLI Reference

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--source` | (required) | Path to source AWS project folder |
| `--dest` | (required) | Path for output Databricks project |
| `--catalog` | `production` | Target Unity Catalog name |
| `--org` | `acme` | Organization name (used in bundle config) |
| `--ai` | off | Enable AI enhancement (databricks-claude-opus-4-6) |
| `--ai-model` | `opus` | Model tier: `opus` (best), `sonnet` (balanced), `haiku` (fast) |
| `--threads` | `1` | Parallel threads for AI calls |
| `--dry-run` | off | Preview specs without writing artifacts |
| `--clean` | off | Delete destination before generating |
| `--verbose` | off | Show detailed parsing output |

### What Happens (9-Step Pipeline)

```
[1/9] Scan source repository (finds DAGs, Step Functions, EMR, Glue)
[2/9] Parse pipeline metadata (extract schedules, sources, classifications)
[3/9] Auto-generate PipelineSpecs (zero manual YAML)
[4/9] Run factory (6 artifacts per pipeline)
[5/9] Create destination repo structure
[6/9] Write all artifacts
[7/9] Write bundle config, CI/CD, README
[8/9] Generate project-specific documentation (7 docs)
[9/9] AI-enhance with Foundation Models (optional, with --ai)
```

### Output Structure

```
databricks-project/
├── databricks.yml              # DAB bundle config (dev/staging/prod targets)
├── README.md                   # Auto-generated project README
├── .gitignore
├── .github/workflows/deploy.yml
├── src/
│   ├── common/                 # Shared utilities
│   └── pipelines/
│       ├── risk/bronze/        # Domain-specific notebooks
│       ├── lending/bronze/
│       └── customer/bronze/
├── resources/jobs/             # Lakeflow Job YAML configs
├── governance/column_masks/    # MNPI/PII column mask SQL
├── quality/                    # DQ expectations SQL
├── monitoring/                 # Freshness + volume alert SQL
├── tests/validation/           # Migration validation pytest
└── docs/                       # AUTO-GENERATED DOCUMENTATION
    ├── MIGRATION_REPORT.md     # What was migrated, stats, risk profile
    ├── ARCHITECTURE.md         # UC structure, compute strategy
    ├── GOVERNANCE.md           # Actual MNPI/PII controls applied
    ├── INGESTION_PATTERNS.md   # Patterns used (references actual pipelines)
    ├── RUNBOOK.md              # Operations runbook (all pipelines)
    ├── VALIDATION_CHECKLIST.md # Pre/post cutover steps
    ├── WAVE_PLAN.md            # Migration wave assignments
    ├── EXECUTIVE_SUMMARY.md    # AI-generated (with --ai)
    ├── PIPELINE_DESCRIPTIONS.md# AI-generated (with --ai)
    └── MIGRATION_REPORT_ENRICHED.md  # AI-enhanced (with --ai)
```

### Auto-Generated Documentation

Every `migrate.py` run produces **7 project-specific docs** (10 with `--ai`). These are NOT generic templates — they reference your actual pipelines, domains, schedules, and MNPI columns.

| Document | Content |
|----------|---------|
| `MIGRATION_REPORT.md` | Pipeline inventory table, risk profile, deploy instructions |
| `ARCHITECTURE.md` | Unity Catalog schema tree, compute strategy matrix, data flow diagram |
| `GOVERNANCE.md` | MNPI/PII controls applied, access groups, audit configuration |
| `INGESTION_PATTERNS.md` | Which source patterns used, references to actual pipeline code |
| `RUNBOOK.md` | Per-pipeline operations guide grouped by domain, common issues & fixes |
| `VALIDATION_CHECKLIST.md` | Checkboxes for every pipeline, pre/post cutover verification |
| `WAVE_PLAN.md` | Complexity-sorted wave assignments, timeline estimate |

