## End-to-End Migration Workflow

### Phase 1: Discovery & Assessment (Weeks 1-3)

```python
# 1. Run scanners against existing infrastructure
from aws2lakehouse.discovery import PipelineInventory, AirflowScanner, LatencyClassifier
from aws2lakehouse.discovery.dependency_graph import DependencyGraph

inventory = PipelineInventory()
airflow = AirflowScanner()
dags = airflow.scan_folder("/opt/airflow/dags")

# 2. Classify complexity and latency
for pipeline in inventory.pipelines:
    pipeline.complexity = analyzer.score(pipeline)
    pipeline.latency = classifier.classify(pipeline.schedule)

# 3. Build dependency graph
graph = DependencyGraph()
graph.add_from_table_lineage(inventory.pipelines)
print(graph.summary())
print(f"Critical path: {graph.critical_path()}")
print(f"Cycles: {graph.detect_cycles()}")  # Must resolve before migrating

# 4. Generate wave plan
waves = graph.migration_waves(max_per_wave=50)

# 5. Conduct stakeholder interviews (use docs/STAKEHOLDER_TEMPLATES.md)
# 6. Calculate ROI (see ROI Calculator section)
```

### Phase 2: Pilot (Weeks 4-6)

Use the pre-built pilot specs to validate the full pipeline end-to-end:

```python
# Start with the simple pipeline
spec = PipelineSpec.from_yaml("examples/pilot/simple_pipeline.yaml")
artifacts = factory.generate(spec)
# Deploy, run, validate

# Then the complex pipeline (Kafka + MNPI + merge)
spec = PipelineSpec.from_yaml("examples/pilot/complex_pipeline.yaml")
artifacts = factory.generate(spec)
# Deploy, run, validate governance, validate DQ
```

### Phase 3: Batch Migration (Weeks 7-16)

```python
# For each wave, batch-generate from YAML specs
for wave_num in range(1, 7):
    specs_dir = f"specs/wave_{wave_num}/"
    artifacts = factory.generate_batch(specs_dir)
    print(f"Wave {wave_num}: Generated {len(artifacts)} pipelines")
    
    # Deploy all via DABs
    # Run validation suite
    # Monitor dashboard
```

### Phase 4: Cutover & Hardening (Weeks 16-20)

See [Cutover & Hypercare](#cutover--hypercare) section.

