## Orchestration Templates

Pre-built Databricks Workflow patterns for common scenarios.

```python
from aws2lakehouse.workflows import WorkflowTemplates, FolderStructureGenerator

# ── Medallion Pipeline (Bronze → Silver → Gold) ──
yaml = WorkflowTemplates.medallion_pipeline(
    name="risk_medallion",
    domain="risk",
    tables=["trades", "positions", "market_data"],
    catalog="production",
    schedule="0 6 * * *"   # Daily at 6 AM
)
# Generates: parallel bronze tasks, sequential silver, single gold aggregation

# ── Conditional Workflow (DQ gate) ──
yaml = WorkflowTemplates.conditional_workflow(
    name="guarded_ingestion",
    domain="compliance",
    check_notebook="/pipelines/compliance/check_source_quality",
    success_notebook="/pipelines/compliance/ingest_data",
    failure_notebook="/pipelines/compliance/remediate_source"
)

# ── For-Each Pattern (same logic, N tables) ──
yaml = WorkflowTemplates.for_each_workflow(
    name="daily_snapshot",
    domain="lending",
    tables=["applications", "approvals", "disbursements", "payments"],
    notebook_path="/pipelines/lending/daily_snapshot"
)

# ── Backfill Workflow (historical reprocessing) ──
yaml = WorkflowTemplates.backfill_workflow(
    name="backfill_trades",
    table="trade_events",
    start_date="2020-01-01",
    end_date="2024-12-31",
    notebook_path="/pipelines/risk/bronze/trade_events",
    parallelism=5
)

# ── Dual-Write Cutover (zero-downtime migration validation) ──
yaml = WorkflowTemplates.dual_write_cutover(
    name="trade_events",
    domain="risk",
    legacy_notebook="/legacy/emr_trade_events",
    new_notebook="/pipelines/risk/bronze/trade_events",
    validation_notebook="/validation/compare_outputs"
)

# ── Generate project folder structure ──
structure = FolderStructureGenerator()
tree = structure.generate(org="acme", domains=["risk", "lending", "compliance"])
script = structure.generate_setup_script(org="acme", domains=["risk", "lending"])
```

