## Cutover & Hypercare

Three strategies for safe production cutover (see `docs/CUTOVER_PLAYBOOK.md` for full details):

| Strategy | Risk Level | Best For | Rollback Speed |
|----------|-----------|----------|----------------|
| **Dual-Write** | Low | Critical/MNPI pipelines | Instant |
| **Shadow Mode** | Low | High-impact pipelines | Instant (view swap) |
| **Big-Bang** | Medium | Simple batch pipelines | Same-day |

### Dual-Write Pattern (Recommended for Critical Pipelines)

```
[Source] ──┬──> [Legacy Pipeline] ──> [legacy_db.table]
           │                              │
           │                        [Compare Job] ──> Alert if drift
           │                              │
           └──> [New Pipeline] ─────> [new_db.table]
```

1. Run both pipelines in parallel for 2+ weeks
2. Comparison job validates zero drift daily
3. Cutover = disable legacy, point consumers to new table
4. Rollback = re-enable legacy (< 5 minutes)

### Hypercare Monitoring (7-14 days post-cutover)
- Day 1: Verify first run, SLA met, DQ scores stable
- Day 2-7: Monitor dashboard twice daily, spot-check reports
- Day 7: Exit criteria check (7 consecutive successes, no alerts)
- Day 14: Final handoff, archive legacy, update tracking

