## Appendix: YAML Spec Reference

### Complete Field Reference

```yaml
# ═══ IDENTITY ═══
name: string                    # Required. Pipeline identifier
domain: string                  # Business domain (risk, lending, etc.)
owner: string                   # Team email or Slack channel
description: string             # Human-readable description
layer: bronze|silver|gold       # Medallion layer

# ═══ SOURCE ═══
source:
  type: kafka|auto_loader|delta_share|jdbc|mongodb|snowflake|delta_table
  config:
    # Kafka
    topic: string
    secret_scope: string
    starting_offsets: latest|earliest
    max_offsets: string

    # Auto Loader
    path: string                # /Volumes/catalog/schema/volume/
    format: csv|json|parquet|avro|xml
    header: "true"|"false"

    # Delta Share
    share_name: string
    schema: string
    table: string

    # JDBC (PostgreSQL, MySQL, Oracle)
    secret_scope: string
    source_table: string
    partition_column: string
    num_partitions: int

    # MongoDB
    connection_uri_secret: string
    database: string
    collection: string
    pipeline: string            # Aggregation pipeline JSON

    # Snowflake
    secret_scope: string
    warehouse: string
    database: string
    schema: string
    table: string

# ═══ TARGET ═══
target:
  catalog: string               # Unity Catalog catalog name
  schema: string                # Schema name
  table: string                 # Table name (defaults to pipeline name)
  mode: streaming|batch|merge   # Write mode
  partition_by: [string]        # Partition columns
  z_order_by: [string]          # Z-ORDER columns
  merge_keys: [string]          # Keys for MERGE mode
  scd_type: 1|2                 # Slowly changing dimension type
  soft_delete: true|false       # Mark deleted vs physical delete

# ═══ DATA QUALITY ═══
quality:
  - name: string                # Rule identifier
    condition: string           # SQL expression (must evaluate to boolean)
    action: warn|drop|quarantine|fail
    threshold: float            # 0.0-1.0 (what % must pass)

# ═══ GOVERNANCE ═══
governance:
  classification: public|internal|confidential|mnpi
  embargo_hours: int            # Hours before data becomes visible
  mnpi_columns: [string]        # Columns with MNPI data
  column_masks:                 # column_name: masked_value
    column_name: "expression"
  row_filter: string            # SQL condition for row-level filter
  owner_group: string           # Group with unrestricted access

# ═══ COMPUTE ═══
compute:
  type: serverless|job_cluster|existing
  photon: true|false
  node_type: string             # e.g., i3.xlarge
  min_workers: int
  max_workers: int

# ═══ SCHEDULE ═══
schedule:
  cron: string                  # Standard cron (5-field)
  timezone: string              # e.g., America/New_York
  sla_minutes: int              # Max acceptable latency

# ═══ RETRY ═══
retry:
  max_attempts: int             # Default: 3
  backoff_seconds: int          # Default: 60

# ═══ ALERTING ═══
alerting:
  on_failure: [string]          # e.g., [slack:#alerts, pagerduty:team]
  on_sla_breach: [string]
  on_success: [string]

# ═══ DEPENDENCIES ═══
depends_on: [string]            # Upstream pipeline names

# ═══ TRANSFORMATION ═══
transform_sql: string           # Optional SQL for Silver-layer transformation

# ═══ TAGS ═══
tags:
  cost_center: string
  criticality: low|medium|high|critical
  regulatory: string            # e.g., mifid2, sox, gdpr
```

### Pilot Examples

**Simple Pipeline** (`examples/pilot/simple_pipeline.yaml`): CSV file ingestion via Auto Loader into Bronze. Demonstrates basic DQ rules, serverless compute, and scheduling.

**Complex Pipeline** (`examples/pilot/complex_pipeline.yaml`): Kafka streaming with MNPI governance (column masks, row filters, embargo), multi-worker job cluster, PagerDuty alerting, and dependency chaining.

